0x0270.description: Returns Apricorn type to Variable based on the pre-defined array of trees in the Notes column. For example, the white Apricorn from Azalea Town would return 6 to Variable. Defaults to 1 for red Apricorn if undefined

0x0271.name: GiveApricorn
0x0271.description: Gives Apricorn of Quantity if current Apricorn count in the box plus Quantity is <= 99. Returns 0 to Var if Apricorn count = 99 to stop the player from obtaining more than 99

0x0272.name: TextApricorn
0x0272.description: Stores Apricorn Name in String Buffer

0x0287.name: GetPartySlotWithSpecies
0x0287.description: Checks party for the presence of a Pokemon, and returns which slot they are in.

0x028C.name: GetTutorPageQuantity
0x028C.description: Checks the number of pages to display for the tutors in Frontier Access. Returns 0 if there are no learnable moves, 1 if the number of learnable moves is <= 7, else (((number of learnable moves)/6)+1)

0x028D.name: MoveTutorChooseMove
0x028D.description: Choose a move for the Pokémon in Party Slot from Tutor on Page and returns the selected move slot from the list to Variable. Variable equals 0xFFFD if the NEXT button was selected, or 0xFFFE if the player cancels teaching a move

0x0290.name: CheckHeadbuttCompatibility
0x0290.description: Stores 1 into Variable if the Pokémon at the given Party Slot can learn Headbutt.

0x029A.name: GetCurrentMusic
0x029A.description: Returns the currently playing BGM to Variable

0x029D.name: GetItemQuantity
0x029D.description: Returns quantity of Item to Result

0x02AB.name: GetBattleOutcome
0x02AB.description: Checks the outcome of a static encounter, like Mewtwo in Cerulean Cave, and stores the result in Variable

0x02AC.name: GetCurrentWeather
0x02AC.description: Stores the current weather in Variable

0x02BA.name: FollowingPokemonIsEventTrigger
0x02BA.description: Checks if the Pokémon in Party Position matches the criteria for the Event. Stores 1 in Var if true.

0x02C4.name: FloorTrapAnimation
0x02C4.description: Triggers Team Rocket HQ trap-floor's graphical effect in the player's current position

0x02C7.name: TalkFollowingPoke
0x02C7.description: The following Pokémon triggers a random movement, and then a random following message

0x02C9.name: OpenAlphaPuzzle
0x02C9.description: Loads the stone-panel puzzle of Puzzle ID.

0x02CA.name: OpenRuinsofAlphHiddenRoom
0x02CA.description: Something to do with the secret room, not the puzzle trapdoor.

0x02D3.name: BoatAnimation
0x02D3.description: Plays the S.S. Aqua animation of leaving the port. Animation is either 0 or 1, with 0 being Olivine and 1 being Vermilion. X and Y coordinates are for the destination map

0x02D7.name: GetFollowingPokePartySlot
0x02D7.description: Returns the following Pokémon's party slot to Variable. Crashes if there are no alive Pokémon in the party

0x02D8.name: FollowingPokeFlash
0x02D8.description: Makes the following Pokémon flash white

0x02D9.name: CheckPokemonAlive
0x02D9.description: Checks if player has at least 1 not fainted Pokémon, stores the result in Variable

0x02DA.name: CheckFollowingPoke
0x02DA.description: Checks if player has a following Pokémon, stores the result in Variable. Returns False if you have a following Pokémon

0x02DC.name: AdjustFollowingPokeMood
0x02DC.description: Increases or decreases following Pokémon mood with a signed 8-bit Integer. Maximum values are 127 and -127

0x02DD.name: GetBornPokemonPartyPos
0x02DD.description: Checks if the following Pokémon's type matches Type. Returns True if so

0x02DE.name: FollowingPokeJump
0x02DE.description: Makes the following Pokémon jump in place Jumps number of times

0x02DF.name: CheckKurtApricorn
0x02DF.description: Checks if Kurt currently has an Apricorn for turning into a ball. If Result is 1, Kurt has an Apricorn already.

0x02E1.name: GetApricornBallID
0x02E1.description: Gets the ID of the Ball Kurt has made and returns it to Var

0x02E2.name: GetApricornCount
0x02E2.description: Returns how many total Apricorns you have to Var

0x02EA.name: OpenTouchScreen
0x02EA.description: Changes the low screen design to the green Pokéball background

0x02EB.name: CloseTouchScreen
0x02EB.description: Sets the default low screen design

0x02EC.name: YesNoTouchScreen
0x02EC.description: Opens a Yes-No selection, stores player's answer in Variable

0x02ED.name: MultiTouchStandardText
0x02ED.description: Prepares a multiple selection menu with text bank #191, returns selected slot ID in Selection

0x02EE.name: MultiTouchLocalText
0x02EE.description: Prepares a multiple selection menu with local texts, returns selected slot ID in Selection. If Close Status is 1, pressing B will automatically select the last option in the list.

0x02EF.name: CreateMultiTouchBox
0x02EF.description: Adds a box with Multi Box Slot ID showing Text Slot text on the bottom screen and Top Screen Text on the top in a message box. Text depends on whether you use MultiTouchStandardText or MultiTouchLocalText

0x02F1.name: RockSmashItemCheck
0x02F1.description: Checks if an item was generated after using Rock Smash. If Following Poke Status is 0, the bonus granted from the following Pokémon being present is not granted. If an item is generated, Result equals TRUE. The item is returned to Item

0x02F2.name: HeadbuttEncounter
0x02F2.description: Tries to generate a Headbutt encounter. If an encounter is generated, Variable is set to TRUE

0x0305.name: RenderCutscene
0x0305.description:
Renders a cutscene
0 = Ho-Oh appearing from the sky
1 = Lugia bursting out of the waterfall
2 = Arceus stock image cutscene

0x0306.name: ShowLegendaryWing
0x0306.description: Shows the Rainbow Wing (0) or the Silver Wing (1) above the player

0x0308.name: GiveTogepiEgg
0x0308.description: Gives an egg containing a Togepi that knows Extrasensory

0x030A.name: GiveSpikyEaredPichu
0x030A.description: Gives the player a Pichu in Spiky-Eared form

0x030B.name: CheckCurrentRadioSong
0x030B.description: Stores 1 in Result if the current Seq is playing from the Pokégear radio. Stores 0 otherwise.

0x030F.name: SetFollowingPokeStatus
0x030F.description:
0 = Following Pokémon allowed
1 = Following Pokémon unallowed

0x0310.name: OverlayManager
0x0310.description: If Action is 0, load an overlay from the list in the Notes column. Otherwise, unload the overlay

0x0311.name: BugContestControl
0x0311.description: If Action is 0, check to initialize the Bug Catching Contest based on Day. Otherwise, end the Bug Catching Contest

0x0312.name: TextBugContestPlacement
0x0312.description: Stores the name of the person that placed in rank Rank. If the player places at rank Rank, the player's name is stored in string buffer 0. If another Trainer places at rank Rank, the Trainer Class and Trainer name are stored in string buffers 2 and 0 respectively. The obtained Pokemon is stored in string buffer 1, and the score is stored in string buffer 3

0x0313.name: BugContestResults
0x0313.description: Generates the results of the Bug Catching Contest

0x0314.name: TextBugContestPokeNickname
0x0314.description: Stores the name of the captured bug from the Bug Catching Contest in String Buffer. Returns 1 to Variable if the party is already full

0x0315.name: TextBugContestRemainingTime
0x0315.description: Stores remaining time in the Bug Catching Contest in String Buffer

0x0316.name: CheckBugContestParticipant
0x0316.description: Checks if the Participant is participating in the Bug Catching Contest. Returns 1 if true to Variable.

0x031B.name: ShowMomMoney
0x031B.description: Shows mom savings money box at X and Y coordinates of the screen

0x0324.name: UpdateTownMap
0x0324.description:
Updates the town map to include Kanto
1 = Normal, Johto-only view
2 = Whole map, Kanto included

0x032D.name: CheckMomGift
0x032D.description: Checks if there is currently a gift from Mom to be picked up

0x033B.name: CheckPartyPokemonForm
0x033B.description: Checks what form Pokémon at Party Slot position has. The Variable stores the form ID.

0x033D.name: CheckFollowingPokeNextToPlayer
0x033D.description: Checks if the following Pokémon is next to the player in any direction

0x0344.name: CheckJadeOrbRequirements
0x0344.description: Stores 1 in Variable if player has both Kyogre and Groudon in the Pokémon party and they have been caught in Johto, stores 0 otherwise

0x0346.name: CheckMoneyFull

0x034B.name: TextItemLowercase
0x034B.description: Stores Item's lowercase name in String Buffer

0x034C.name: TextItemPlural
0x034C.description: Stores Item's plural noun in String Buffer

0x034D.name: TextPartyPokemonDefault
0x034D.description: Stores the name of the Pokémon in Party Position in String Buffer with default color tags encoding

0x0351.name: TextTrainerClass
0x0351.description: Stores Trainer class' lowercase noun in String Buffer

0x0352.name: TextSealPlural
0x0352.description: Stores Seal's plural noun in String Buffer

0x0353.name: TextCapitalize
0x0353.description: Capitalizes the string currently stored in String Buffer

0x0354.name: TextFloor
0x0354.description: Stores Floor's name in String Buffer
